<item>
            <title>[LU-19095] Target notifies MGS about LNet changes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19095</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Related to the work in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10360&quot; title=&quot;use Imperative Recovery logs for client-&amp;gt;MDT/OST connections&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10360&quot;&gt;LU-10360&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10359&quot; title=&quot;remove NIDs from config llogs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10359&quot;&gt;LU-10359&lt;/a&gt;, it is important that dynamically configured server NIDs that are added after MDT/OSTs are mounted are advertised to the MGS IR logs, so that clients which mount the filesystem at this point are able to see which NIDs can be used to contact the targets. &#160;These NIDs would &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; be stored in the permanent MGS config llog, only in the dynamic MGS IR log that &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10360&quot; title=&quot;use Imperative Recovery logs for client-&amp;gt;MDT/OST connections&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10360&quot;&gt;LU-10360&lt;/a&gt; is using to inform the client about target NIDs.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Implement mechanism to get LNet notifications on target about network changes and send notification to MGS IR table about target NIDs changes&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
